author: The Associated Press
title: Police arrest Wisconsin homicide suspect in Lakewood
text:
Police arrest Wisconsin homicide suspect in Lakewood   9:55 am A man wanted in a fatal shooting in southern Wisconsin has been arrested in Lakewood. By The Associated Press 
BELOIT, Wis. — Police say a second man has been arrested for a fatal shooting in southern Wisconsin last year. 
Authorities caught up with the man in Lakewood, Washington this week after getting a tip from someone who provided an address. A warrant for the man’s arrest on second-degree reckless homicide was issued in Rock County following the April 2014 death of Raymond Holloway. He was shot and killed while standing outside his grandmother’s house in Beloit. 
Another man, Jajuan Logan, was earlier convicted in Holloway’s death and was sentenced to 12 years in prison. The Associated Press
